The '''Corruption Panel''' was a body of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[New Republic Senate/Legends|Senate]] that oversaw and reviewed the conduct of [[Senator/Legends|senators]] and other representatives. In [[26 ABY/Legends|26 ABY]] it was headed by [[Kvarm Jia]] and [[E'noro]] sat on the panel. It was charged with investigating the [[Kuat/Legends|Kuati]] senator [[Viqi Shesh]] prior to the [[Peace Vote|Appeasement Vote]].

It was based in the [[Senate Inquiry Room]] of the [[Senate Building/Legends|Senate Building]].

